
<p><i>Then the Ten Commandments may be said, or the following</i></p>
<p>Hear what our Lord Jesus Christ saith:</p>
<p>Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with<br/>all thy soul, and with all thy mind.  This is the first and great<br/>commandment.  And the second is like unto it:  Thou shalt<br/>love thy neighbor as thyself.  On these two commandments<br/>hang all the Law and the Prophets.</p>
<p><i>Here is sung or said</i></p>
<p>Lord, have mercy upon us.<br/><i>Christ, have mercy upon us.</i><br/>Lordhave mercy upon us.</p>
<p><i>or</i></p>
<p>Kyrie eleison.<br/><i>Christe eleison.</i><br/>Kyrie eleison.</p>
<p><i>or this</i></p>
<p>Holy God,<br/>Holy and Mighty,<br/>Holy Immortal One,<br/><i>Have mercy upon us.</i></p>
<p><i>When appointed, the following hymn or some other song of praise is sung<br/>or said, in addition to, or in place of, the preceding, all standing</i></p>
<p>Glory be to God on high,<br/>  and on earth peace, good will towards men.</p>
<p>We praise thee, we bless the,<br/>  we worship thee,<br/>  we glorify thee,<br/>we give thanks to thee for thy great glory,<br/>O Lord God, heavenly King, God the Father Almighty.</p>
<p>O Lord, the only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ;<br/>O Lord God, Lamb of God, Son of the Father,<br/>  that takest away the sins of the world,<br/>  have mercy upon us.</p>
    